<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,391,525]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,391,416]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[276,560,392,416]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" refId="ref47771" refString="Massa, B. &amp; Fontana, P. (2011) Supraspecific taxonomy of Palaearctic Platycleidini with unarmed prosternum: a morphological approach (Orthoptera: Tettigoniidae, Tettigoniinae). Zootaxa, 2837, 1 - 47." type="journal article">Massa &amp; Fontana (2011)</bibRefCitation>
raised all subgenera of 
<emphasis box="[837,982,391,416]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<taxonomicName authority="Ünal, 2018" authorityName="Ünal" authorityYear="2018" box="[837,948,391,416]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Platycleis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="lato" status="s.l">Platycleis</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[956,982,391,416]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" sensu="lato">s.l</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[1041,1217,391,416]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<taxonomicName authority="Ünal, 2018" authorityName="Ünal" authorityYear="2018" box="[1041,1176,393,416]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Metrioptera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="lato" status="s.l.">Metrioptera</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1185,1217,391,416]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" sensu="lato">s.l.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
to genus level and mentioned the disagreement of researchers about the statuses of these taxa. These genera are placed under generic groups in 
<bibRefCitation box="[263,489,463,488]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" refId="ref45958" refString="Cigliano, M. M., Braun, H., Eades, D. C. &amp; Otte, D. (2018) Orthoptera Species File, Version 5.0 / 5.0. Available from: http: // Orthoptera. SpeciesFile. org (accessed 21 March 2018)" type="url">
Cigliano 
<emphasis box="[366,423,463,488]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
. Because of the close relationships of these taxa I prefer to preserve their subgeneric statuses and follow 
<bibRefCitation box="[373,508,500,525]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" refId="ref46567" refString="Harz, K. (1969) The Orthoptera of Europe (Die Orthopteren Europas 1). Series entomologica 5. Dr. W. Junk N. V, The Hague, 749 pp." type="book">Harz (1969)</bibRefCitation>
in the present study.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
